content:
Data packs use a custom metadata object called a Vlocity Matching Key to define the uniqueness of any SObject.

For Example, a Product2 in data packs is unique by the vlocity_namespace__GlobalKey__c field by default. If your org has a different field that is used for uniqueness like ProductCode, you can override this matching key, and use your unique field instead.

Vlocity Matching Keys are a custom metadata type in Salesforce. Vlocity matching keys contain seven fields

You can find the matching key fields by the Object API or Command Line API which can also return JSON formatted output and accept some inputs as JSON.

You can change the settings that are used to define the behavior of each data pack that is imported, deployed, and written to the files.
title: Creating Custom Matching Keys in Salesforce
